                <div2 xml:id="africa.question">
                    <head>Africa(n) Question</head>
                    <p>By the African Question, the project refers to the act of colonizing Africa, but more significantly, the transnational debate over the future of Africa under European control.</p>
                </div2>
                
                
                <listPerson>
                    
                    <person xml:id="bright.jacob">
                        <persName>
                            <forename type="first">Jacob</forename>
                            <surname>Bright</surname>
                        </persName>
                        <birth when="1821-05-26">1821</birth>
                        <death when="1899-11-07">1899</death>
                        <note>Jacob Bright was a member of the British Parliament, representing the Borough of Manchester from 1867-1874 and from 1876-1885. From 1886-1895, he represented the Southwest Division of Manchester. Bright was a Liberal who challenged Prime Minister William Ewart Gladstone's support of a treaty that would recognize Portugal's control over both sides of the Congo River. Bright successfully prevented ratification of the Congo Treaty in the House of Commons.</note>
                    </person>
                    
                    <person xml:id="bismarck.otto">
                        <persName>
                            <forename>Otto</forename>
