                        <note>Cura&#199;çao-born, Jewish intellectual Daniel DeLeon joined the Socialist Party in 1890 while in the United States. He began working with the American Federation of Labor, but in 1895, left the group to form the Socialist Trade and Labor Alliance.</note>
