                    <org xml:id="con.ber">
                        <orgName>Berlin Conference</orgName>            
                        <desc>The Berlin Conference was a gathering of European powers to reach an agreement regarding the free navigation of the Congo and Niger rivers and to establish procedures for future European claims to territory in Africa. Held during the winter of 1884-85, dignitaries representing the United States, Belgium, Spain, Denmark, France, Italy, the United Kingdom, Austria-Hungary, the Netherlands, Russia, Portugal, the Ottoman Empire, and the United Kingdoms of Norway and Sweden gathered in Berlin.</desc>
                    </org>
                    
